    <string name="home_delay_info_desc">Info about wearing the ring longer</string>
    <string name="home_delay_info_message"><![CDATA[
            <b>You forgot to remove the ring</b><br><br>
            <b>Ring in for 3–4 weeks</b>: Contraceptive protection remains. Remove the ring, take a ring-free week (when bleeding usually occurs), then insert a new ring.<br><br>
            <b>Ring in for longer than 4 weeks</b>: Contraceptive protection may be reduced — there is a risk of pregnancy. Remove the ring immediately and contact your doctor before inserting a new one (a pregnancy test or additional contraception may be needed).<br><br>
            <b>Note</b>: If bleeding does not occur after removing the ring, seek medical advice as well.<br><br>
            ]]></string>
