    <string name="home_skip_ring_free_confirm">Skip now</string>
    <string name="home_skip_ring_free_info_desc">Info about skipping the ring-free week</string>
    <string name="home_skip_ring_free_info_message"><![CDATA[
            <b>You want to delay your period</b><br><br>
            This is not the recommended standard use, but it is possible:<br>
            - Skip the ring-free week and insert a new ring immediately after removing the old one.<br>
            - The new ring can stay in place for up to 3 weeks.<br>
            - During this time, spotting or breakthrough bleeding may occur.<br>
            - To trigger withdrawal bleeding: remove the ring earlier, take the usual one-week ring-free break, then insert a new ring.<br><br>
            <b>Important</b>: Ask your doctor for advice before delaying your period.
            ]]></string>
    <string name="home_skip_ring_free_message">After ring removal, the next insertion is set immediately for this cycle. The following cycles continue normally with a ring-free week.</string>
